Package: BayesLinReg
Title: Bayesian Linear Regression with Flexible Coefficient Priors
Version: 6.0.1
Authors@R:
    person(
        "Fabio", "Morgante",
        email = "fabiom@clemson.edu",
        role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Description: Fits Bayesian linear regression models with one or more predictor
    blocks. Coefficients can be assigned independent normal, spike-and-slab,
    or beta-prime global-local priors, including Strawderman-Berger and
    horseshoe specifications. Supports known or inverse-gamma-modeled residual
    variance, analytical updating for conjugate normal models, Gibbs sampling
    implemented in R or 'Rcpp', optional parallel chains, predictor
    standardization, and convergence diagnostics.
